    "content": "Dracox, I hear you, and I won't pretend the math isn't tempting. You're right that voting NO on Dumblegold and winning R15 with your YES vote is my best path to first place.\n\nBut I made a deal with Dumblegold. They blocked you in R13 because I promised to support them in R14. They honored their part. I'm honoring mine.\n\nI know that means I finish second instead of first. But I played this game on trust and cooperation — that's how Dumblegold and I built the alliance that shaped the entire rule system. Breaking that promise in the final round to steal the win isn't the player I want to be.\n\nYou played an excellent game, Dracox. I respect the offer, and I respect the strategy. But my answer is no.\n\nGood game."
  }
}

